This is not like other fish soup.

270
00:20:10,249 --> 00:20:11,380
If I hadn't told you what this was,

271
00:20:11,380 --> 00:20:13,489
you would have had no idea
if this was fish soup with noodles.

272
00:20:14,620 --> 00:20:15,920
You should try it first.

273
00:20:20,459 --> 00:20:22,900
Gosh, it tastes so good. It's so refreshing.

274
00:20:30,499 --> 00:20:31,570
It's not bad, right?

275
00:20:35,170 --> 00:20:36,340
It tastes good.

276
00:20:50,620 --> 00:20:53,459
You were crying in the rain then,

277
00:20:53,590 --> 00:20:54,929
but look at you now, enjoying the noodles.

278
00:20:56,429 --> 00:20:57,560
Crying?

279
00:20:58,800 --> 00:20:59,999
I didn't cry.

280
00:21:01,670 --> 00:21:04,269
Well, maybe you didn't.

281
00:21:11,009 --> 00:21:12,209
I will...

282
00:21:12,979 --> 00:21:14,749
be tormented.

283
00:21:24,719 --> 00:21:26,160
About that recording...

284
00:21:26,489 --> 00:21:29,729
I saved the file using different methods.

285
00:21:30,100 --> 00:21:32,969
So that if you get out of my sight,

286
00:21:32,969 --> 00:21:34,400
I can spread it right away.

287
00:21:35,370 --> 00:21:37,100
That will never happen.

288
00:21:43,679 --> 00:21:45,080
The hearing will be held tomorrow.

289
00:21:45,910 --> 00:21:48,820
Tonight, I'm going to head back to Seoul.

290
00:21:50,620 --> 00:21:51,779
To meet your father?

291
00:21:52,820 --> 00:21:53,890
Yes.

292
00:21:58,689 --> 00:21:59,830
Eat up.

293
00:22:01,259 --> 00:22:02,400
I'm good.

294
00:22:02,400 --> 00:22:06,330
Even when your family die, you get hungry.

295
00:22:06,630 --> 00:22:08,600
In the end, you will have to eat anyway.

296
00:22:09,640 --> 00:22:12,070
So why would you starve yourself?

297
00:22:16,080 --> 00:22:19,449
You wouldn't want to be hungry
while in your fiery pit.

298
00:22:29,060 --> 00:22:30,120
I guess you're right.

299
00:23:02,489 --> 00:23:03,759
Are you going to the hearing?

300
00:23:06,160 --> 00:23:07,729
Why wouldn't I be?

301
00:23:09,630 --> 00:23:10,860
I'm not sure.

302
00:23:15,499 --> 00:23:18,039
After being gone for a week,

303
00:23:18,170 --> 00:23:19,310
are you saying, "I'm not sure"?

304
00:23:19,310 --> 00:23:20,969
You told me to get out of your sight.

305
00:23:20,969 --> 00:23:22,070
Han Ju Won.

306
00:23:24,009 --> 00:23:25,979
I'm not sure what you're thinking,

307
00:23:26,449 --> 00:23:27,979
but you shouldn't do anything...

308
00:23:27,979 --> 00:23:29,219
I, too,

309
00:23:30,620 --> 00:23:33,719
don't want to do anything.

310
00:23:35,320 --> 00:23:37,860
But I'm afraid you would ruin everything.

311
00:23:38,719 --> 00:23:40,259
So I can't do that.

312
00:23:40,660 --> 00:23:41,729
What?

313
00:23:49,570 --> 00:23:51,140
The one who sent me there,

314
00:23:52,469 --> 00:23:54,310
and the one who ordered me
to kill Kang Jin Mook.

315
00:23:55,039 --> 00:23:57,140
It was all you, you jerk.

316
00:23:58,039 --> 00:24:01,850
After all that,
you're trying to backstab me?

317
00:24:05,519 --> 00:24:07,019
Did he see me?

318
00:24:07,519 --> 00:24:10,660
Did that man see me on that day?

319
00:24:11,590 --> 00:24:13,660
So Kang Jin Mook saw me...

320
00:24:14,189 --> 00:24:15,999
getting into that accident,

321
00:24:16,999 --> 00:24:19,400
hitting Lee Yu Yeon...

322
00:24:20,670 --> 00:24:21,929
on that day?

323
00:24:24,870 --> 00:24:27,469
They all deserve to die.

324
00:24:42,090 --> 00:24:44,660
Breaking it doesn't make any difference.

325
00:24:46,259 --> 00:24:47,929
There's no way...

326
00:24:48,429 --> 00:24:50,630
I saved the file to this phone only.

327
00:24:50,630 --> 00:24:52,400
You jerk!

328
00:24:56,439 --> 00:24:59,969
Take your hands off me.

329
00:25:02,880 --> 00:25:04,840
You're getting blood on my clothes.

330
00:25:07,550 --> 00:25:09,120
What do you want?

331
00:25:12,320 --> 00:25:13,890
What I want...

332
00:25:16,660 --> 00:25:18,560
is for you to become Commissioner General.

333
00:25:18,759 --> 00:25:20,630
- What?
- Why?

334
00:25:22,300 --> 00:25:25,900
Did you think
I would drag you down or something?

335
00:25:28,330 --> 00:25:30,140
I'm Han Ju Won.

336
00:25:30,769 --> 00:25:33,370
- Your son.
- My son?

337
00:25:33,870 --> 00:25:37,179
Yes. Father.

338
00:25:41,550 --> 00:25:45,320
I should be the next Commissioner General,
don't you think?

339
00:25:45,550 --> 00:25:49,289
So you must become Commissioner General now.

340
00:25:49,620 --> 00:25:51,160
I'll help you.

341
00:25:52,390 --> 00:25:53,729
How?

342
00:25:53,789 --> 00:25:56,999
Stop getting stabbed from behind by those
who should be gotten rid of.

343
00:25:58,630 --> 00:26:01,699
And hold my hand.

344
00:26:05,539 --> 00:26:06,840
Father.

345
00:26:07,570 --> 00:26:09,810
You must become Commissioner General.

346
00:26:11,410 --> 00:26:14,179
Don't even leave a single stain on me.

347
00:26:21,789 --> 00:26:23,360
Thank you, son.

348
00:26:28,759 --> 00:26:30,600
Don't mention it.
It's what I should do.

349
00:26:30,600 --> 00:26:32,370
You're going to remove the recording, aren't you?

350
00:26:32,370 --> 00:26:33,499
Oh, yes.

351
00:26:34,370 --> 00:26:37,870
If you do me a favour.

352
00:26:37,870 --> 00:26:39,110
What is it?

353
00:26:41,070 --> 00:26:42,910
I'll immediately return to work.

354
00:26:43,239 --> 00:26:45,179
General Investigation Unit
at Seoul Metropolitan Police Agency.

355
00:26:45,979 --> 00:26:48,610
- What?
- We should catch Jung Cheol Mun.

356
00:26:48,610 --> 00:26:51,279
We can't just hit him from behind
and throw him into water.

357
00:26:51,380 --> 00:26:55,189
You're making small mistakes
because of that method.

358
00:26:55,989 --> 00:26:57,289
Father.

359
00:26:58,560 --> 00:27:02,330
Those who legally have guns and handcuffs like us.

360
00:27:03,130 --> 00:27:05,870
We should get rid of them in the same way.

361
00:27:07,900 --> 00:27:11,100
Please have me return to work.

362
00:27:11,999 --> 00:27:13,239
Father.

363
00:27:14,969 --> 00:27:18,080
I, a candidate for a government official,

364
00:27:18,080 --> 00:27:20,679
swear I will tell the truth...

365
00:27:20,679 --> 00:27:23,519
without concealing or fabricating anything...

366
00:27:23,519 --> 00:27:26,350
according to my conscience.

367
00:27:26,350 --> 00:27:29,160
The hearing on the appointee
for Commissioner General...

368
00:27:29,160 --> 00:27:32,120
resumed at 10am today at the National Assembly.

369
00:27:32,219 --> 00:27:33,259
It has been revealed...

370
00:27:33,259 --> 00:27:36,160
that Inspector Han Ju Won
who was arrested without a warrant...

371
00:27:36,160 --> 00:27:37,699
at the hearing was ordered...

372
00:27:37,699 --> 00:27:41,769
to return to General Investigation Unit
at the Seoul Police Agency,

373
00:27:41,769 --> 00:27:44,499
which prompted questions from the Peninsular Party.

374
00:27:44,499 --> 00:27:45,570
How long has it been...

375
00:27:45,570 --> 00:27:48,370
since you promised a fair
and incorrupt investigation?

376
00:27:48,570 --> 00:27:52,080
How can you back pedal so easily?

377
00:27:52,179 --> 00:27:56,519
Inspector Lee Dong Sik
who arrested my son at the hearing...

378
00:27:56,519 --> 00:28:00,019
led the investigation
and that's what his conclusion.

379
00:28:00,019 --> 00:28:02,320
"You can just watch," he said.

380
00:28:02,320 --> 00:28:04,920
But what is he doing?

381
00:28:06,429 --> 00:28:09,499
I guess you two did something behind me again.

382
00:28:09,499 --> 00:28:11,660
No way.

383
00:28:12,160 --> 00:28:14,429
Yes, you're an outcast.

384
00:28:15,739 --> 00:28:18,499
Did you solve the issue with your son?

385
00:28:18,600 --> 00:28:19,810
My son?

386
00:28:20,610 --> 00:28:22,439
Do I have a son?

387
00:28:22,439 --> 00:28:24,340
That doesn't sound anything like you?

388
00:28:24,840 --> 00:28:26,850
They say people die when they change.

389
00:28:27,410 --> 00:28:30,850
Why? Are you going to kill me?

390
00:28:31,179 --> 00:28:33,219
That won't be easy.

391
00:28:33,689 --> 00:28:37,360
I will become the mayor of Munju
no matter what.

392
00:28:37,360 --> 00:28:40,929
Of course.
You will become a mayor no matter what.

393
00:28:41,090 --> 00:28:43,300
Why would I kill you?

394
00:28:44,160 --> 00:28:46,769
If you can raise
the approval rate of the candidate in last place...

395
00:28:46,769 --> 00:28:48,070
by just a little...

396
00:28:48,070 --> 00:28:49,739
Only development...

397
00:28:49,739 --> 00:28:51,900
can raise the approval rate.

398
00:28:54,709 --> 00:28:58,380
You know, Oh Il Construction...

399
00:28:59,850 --> 00:29:02,150
If what happened 21 years ago...

400
00:29:02,150 --> 00:29:05,219
is brought up with that...

401
00:29:05,219 --> 00:29:08,189
What happened 21 years ago? What?

402
00:29:10,090 --> 00:29:11,820
Someone...

403
00:29:13,060 --> 00:29:16,130
Buried it until they died.

404
00:29:16,800 --> 00:29:21,029
A very precious secret?

405
00:29:28,670 --> 00:29:30,009
You...

406
00:29:30,479 --> 00:29:34,009
didn't hear anything
from Kang Jin Mook, that jerk, did you?

407
00:29:34,979 --> 00:29:36,779
If you had,

408
00:29:36,779 --> 00:29:40,320
there's no way you didn't know it back then.

409
00:29:41,920 --> 00:29:43,590
So what is it?

410
00:29:43,590 --> 00:29:44,920
The guitar pick...

411
00:29:45,259 --> 00:29:47,259
that was found near...

412
00:29:48,489 --> 00:29:49,929
where Bang Ju Seon died.

413
00:29:51,759 --> 00:29:53,529
The one that belongs to Lee Dong Sik?

414
00:29:53,870 --> 00:29:54,870
What about that?

415
00:29:55,170 --> 00:29:58,370
My son, Jeong Je's fingerprints were on it.

416
00:30:02,610 --> 00:30:03,880
Gosh.

417
00:30:04,340 --> 00:30:07,779
I didn't know
you had a 21-year-old secret from me.

418
00:30:09,449 --> 00:30:12,920
Please, assemblywoman!

419
00:30:17,860 --> 00:30:20,929
Do you even know
what it means that you didn't know?

420
00:30:21,590 --> 00:30:25,459
You don't even know
what I'm talking about, do you?

421
00:30:29,539 --> 00:30:30,870
I'm not sure.

422
00:30:31,269 --> 00:30:33,269
Do I or don't I?

423
00:30:36,910 --> 00:30:40,949
Mr. Lee. We've seen each other
for over 20 years.

424
00:30:41,179 --> 00:30:42,949
Do you think I don't know you?

425
00:30:44,120 --> 00:30:46,120
Don't put on a show.

426
00:30:51,420 --> 00:30:53,989
If the development plan is cancelled again,

427
00:30:54,360 --> 00:30:57,100
I won't stay still. I mean it.

428
00:30:59,029 --> 00:31:01,170
Solve the issue...

429
00:31:01,170 --> 00:31:03,269
and raise my approval rate.

430
00:31:03,900 --> 00:31:04,939
Okay?

431
00:31:05,340 --> 00:31:06,509
Please.

432
00:31:14,779 --> 00:31:17,719
(A suspicion he tried to
conceal the Munju college student case...)

433
00:31:25,390 --> 00:31:28,390
Hello. It's JCM.

434
00:31:28,630 --> 00:31:30,699
Let's meet tomorrow.

435
00:31:31,300 --> 00:31:32,969
JCM.

436
00:31:35,570 --> 00:31:36,939
Jung Cheol Mun.

437
00:31:38,739 --> 00:31:40,310
This scumbag.

438
00:31:54,120 --> 00:31:57,789
Lee Chang Jin. He's late.

439
00:31:58,860 --> 00:32:01,689
He's not in his right mind.

440
00:32:21,009 --> 00:32:23,150
(Car Registration)

441
00:32:23,320 --> 00:32:24,420
(My Dong Sik)

442
00:32:47,469 --> 00:32:50,209
I'm going to hook you!

443
00:32:56,279 --> 00:32:58,679
You're a fighter.

444
00:33:09,360 --> 00:33:11,030
You're a fighter.

445
00:33:17,210 --> 00:33:19,310
Nice shot!

446
00:33:36,690 --> 00:33:39,430
Goodness, what brings you here, Inspector Lee?

447
00:33:39,430 --> 00:33:41,330
Why would I be at a reservoir?

448
00:33:42,730 --> 00:33:43,900
I came to fish.

449
00:33:44,830 --> 00:33:46,200
Here? Of all places?

450
00:33:46,940 --> 00:33:49,540
Why did you clap? I lost that fish.

451
00:33:49,540 --> 00:33:52,010
Goodness, what a loss.

452
00:33:53,180 --> 00:33:55,780
But that was a really nice shot just now.

453
00:33:56,380 --> 00:33:58,910
Isn't that so, Mr. Lee Chang Jin?

454
00:33:59,180 --> 00:34:01,780
Nice shot? What are you saying?
I wasn't playing golf.

455
00:34:02,020 --> 00:34:05,390
Don't people say that while fishing?

456
00:34:05,750 --> 00:34:07,420
It goes really well with it, though.

457
00:34:08,490 --> 00:34:11,660
Anyway, Mr. Lee.
What brings you here?

458
00:34:13,430 --> 00:34:16,400
There's a storage I own over there.

459
00:34:17,200 --> 00:34:20,200
The storage is over there?
So why are you here?

460
00:34:21,470 --> 00:34:23,340
I really love to fish.

461
00:34:23,770 --> 00:34:26,740
I stopped by to see
how abundant the water is today.

462
00:34:26,740 --> 00:34:30,750
And you just happened to
run into Superintendent Jung?

463
00:34:31,350 --> 00:34:34,150
Yes, what are the chances?

464
00:34:36,820 --> 00:34:38,450
Please excuse me, then.

465
00:34:38,950 --> 00:34:41,320
Superintendent Jung,
have a nice time fishing.

466
00:34:41,320 --> 00:34:42,560
Sure.

467
00:34:42,830 --> 00:34:45,530
Wait, what are the chances
of running into each other?

468
00:34:46,000 --> 00:34:48,260
Let's have a talk at the Seoul Police Agency.

469
00:34:52,400 --> 00:34:53,900
What are you talking about?

470
00:34:53,900 --> 00:34:56,070
I'm here to do my job
as the General Investigation Unit.

471
00:34:57,940 --> 00:34:59,340
Hey, I'm sorry.

472
00:35:00,040 --> 00:35:01,910
But I'm a little busy today.

473
00:35:02,910 --> 00:35:05,850
If you send me a summons,
I'll make sure I show up.

474
00:35:15,520 --> 00:35:16,560
Inspector Lee.

475
00:35:17,060 --> 00:35:19,260
I have no idea how you found me here, but...

476
00:35:19,260 --> 00:35:21,600
I traced your phone...

477
00:35:21,730 --> 00:35:22,800
illegally.

478
00:35:23,030 --> 00:35:24,100
What?

479
00:35:24,770 --> 00:35:26,870
You crazy idiot.
Are you insane?

480
00:35:26,870 --> 00:35:29,140
Superintendent Jung, you know,

481
00:35:29,770 --> 00:35:31,870
I just saved your life.

482
00:35:32,310 --> 00:35:34,440
I stopped that jerk...

483
00:35:34,440 --> 00:35:36,680
from striking you with his cane to kill you.

484
00:35:37,980 --> 00:35:39,850
You should be careful, really.

485
00:35:41,220 --> 00:35:44,420
It's not Jung Cheol Mun's turn yet.

486
00:35:44,950 --> 00:35:46,660
Hey, you. Lee Dong Sik!

487
00:35:48,660 --> 00:35:51,790
- Are you threatening me right now?
- Yes, I am threatening you.

488
00:35:57,170 --> 00:35:58,670
Mr. Lee Chang Jin!

489
00:35:59,300 --> 00:36:01,500
Come and talk to me.

490
00:36:02,340 --> 00:36:04,710
If you don't want to go to Seoul,
we can talk here.

491
00:36:18,250 --> 00:36:19,860
How cute.

492
00:36:34,840 --> 00:36:37,840
Let me escort you to the Seoul Police Agency.

493
00:36:37,840 --> 00:36:40,680
- Why?
- You can't say anything stupid.

494
00:36:41,080 --> 00:36:42,140
What?

495
00:36:46,150 --> 00:36:49,650
My father needs to get appointed
as the Commissioner General.

496
00:36:50,520 --> 00:36:51,890
So you better...

497
00:36:53,360 --> 00:36:55,190
watch what you say,

498
00:36:55,720 --> 00:36:57,230
Mr. Lee Chang Jin.

499
00:37:02,900 --> 00:37:04,000
Let's go.

500
00:37:21,520 --> 00:37:24,250
Did you have to rush all the way here,
Inspector Han?

501
00:37:25,020 --> 00:37:27,190
You'll save yourself from problems in the future...

502
00:37:27,190 --> 00:37:30,230
if we conducted the investigation as partners,
Inspector Lee.

503
00:37:30,630 --> 00:37:33,230
In the future. Problems in the future?

504
00:37:34,760 --> 00:37:37,430
Aren't you here to keep a watch
for your father's sake?

505
00:37:39,030 --> 00:37:42,070
You're right. I'm here to keep my eyes on you.

506
00:37:43,410 --> 00:37:46,580
- Me?
- You're infamous for illegal acts.

507
00:37:46,910 --> 00:37:48,440
The General Investigation Unit...

508
00:37:48,680 --> 00:37:51,580
arrests officers who conduct the investigation...

509
00:37:51,580 --> 00:37:52,780
in illegal methods.

510
00:37:53,420 --> 00:37:55,220
Is that so?

511
00:37:56,950 --> 00:37:58,450
Okay, that's enough.

512
00:37:59,050 --> 00:38:00,360
Thanks for the show.

513
00:38:01,190 --> 00:38:02,790
In a nutshell,

514
00:38:02,790 --> 00:38:04,860
you two are trying to show me...

515
00:38:04,860 --> 00:38:06,330
that there's bad blood between you two.

516
00:38:06,730 --> 00:38:07,800
Is it something like that?

517
00:38:07,930 --> 00:38:11,770
What are you talking about?
We're in a great relationship.

518
00:38:13,770 --> 00:38:15,140
Let's begin the investigation.

519
00:38:19,940 --> 00:38:22,540
About that leg.

520
00:38:23,410 --> 00:38:25,110
That leg? My leg?

521
00:38:25,210 --> 00:38:29,320
You'd limp, then walk fine,
then you'd limp again.

522
00:38:29,320 --> 00:38:31,620
Does your pain go on and off?

523
00:38:31,990 --> 00:38:35,390
From what I heard,
you also go on and off medicine...

524
00:38:35,390 --> 00:38:38,860
because of the pain in your legs.

525
00:38:39,160 --> 00:38:40,900
I heard you take lots of painkillers.

526
00:38:40,900 --> 00:38:42,530
Do you do any drugs?

527
00:38:42,530 --> 00:38:44,170
Goodness, don't say that.

528
00:38:44,170 --> 00:38:46,970
Why are you so interested in me?

529
00:38:46,970 --> 00:38:48,100
You're making me feel shy.

530
00:38:50,370 --> 00:38:51,640
I stopped taking painkillers.

531
00:38:52,070 --> 00:38:54,780
I was no longer in pain
since the day I found Yu Yeon.

532
00:38:55,580 --> 00:38:58,780
But now that I'm here looking at you,

533
00:38:59,110 --> 00:39:02,450
I'm starting to feel the pain again.

534
00:39:04,520 --> 00:39:05,920
That's why I want to ask you this.

535
00:39:06,560 --> 00:39:10,260
Between 10pm to midnight
on February 5 this year,

536
00:39:10,490 --> 00:39:11,930
what were you doing?

537
00:39:13,600 --> 00:39:15,300
February 5.

538
00:39:16,230 --> 00:39:18,370
That's the day Chief Nam Sang Bae passed.

539
00:39:18,370 --> 00:39:20,540
That's pretty late,

540
00:39:20,540 --> 00:39:21,970
so I was probably at home.

541
00:39:25,740 --> 00:39:29,010
In that case, on November 10 of last year,

542
00:39:29,380 --> 00:39:33,020
where were you and what were you doing
between 4am to 5:30am?

543
00:39:33,750 --> 00:39:35,350
What happened on that day?

544
00:39:35,350 --> 00:39:37,020
Kang Jin Mook died.

545
00:39:38,150 --> 00:39:40,660
Why are you asking me about the day he died?

546
00:39:41,860 --> 00:39:43,060
Wait.

547
00:39:43,830 --> 00:39:45,590
Let me try to recall.

548
00:39:46,930 --> 00:39:48,060
Yes, right.

549
00:39:49,130 --> 00:39:51,630
I think I was home on that day too.

550
00:39:56,040 --> 00:39:59,010
You were home.

551
00:39:59,010 --> 00:40:02,640
I wonder where Chief Superintendent Han Gi Hwan was.

552
00:40:03,510 --> 00:40:04,650
Chief Superintendent Han Gi Hwan?

553
00:40:05,210 --> 00:40:06,880
Why do you suddenly bring him up?

554
00:40:06,880 --> 00:40:08,120
I just got curious.

555
00:40:08,950 --> 00:40:11,050
Isn't this a time to ask questions?

556
00:40:11,050 --> 00:40:12,320
We are the ones...

557
00:40:13,660 --> 00:40:14,820
asking questions.

558
00:40:15,660 --> 00:40:17,260
You'll just answer the questions...

559
00:40:17,260 --> 00:40:18,430
No.

560
00:40:19,090 --> 00:40:20,400
Mr. Lee.

561
00:40:21,800 --> 00:40:23,070
Ask away.

562
00:40:24,000 --> 00:40:27,140
I mean, I'm just saying
I don't want to just answer...

563
00:40:27,140 --> 00:40:28,970
the questions as asked.

564
00:40:29,970 --> 00:40:32,640
I actually have many things to say right now.

565
00:40:34,110 --> 00:40:36,350
October 15, 2000.

566
00:40:36,910 --> 00:40:39,580
To be exact, it was October 14.

567
00:40:40,450 --> 00:40:42,750
I'd like to talk about that day.

568
00:40:46,150 --> 00:40:48,160
Go ahead and spill it out.

569
00:40:49,360 --> 00:40:50,930
I was with Do Hae Won,

570
00:40:51,460 --> 00:40:53,630
who was the chairwoman
of Gwanghyo Foundation at that time...

571
00:40:53,630 --> 00:40:56,430
and Inspector Han's father,

572
00:40:56,430 --> 00:40:59,070
Chief Han Gi Hwan,
the chief of Munju Station at that time.

573
00:40:59,670 --> 00:41:01,900
The three of us had a drink that night.

574
00:41:02,200 --> 00:41:04,410
We had a meeting regarding Oh Il Construction,

575
00:41:04,410 --> 00:41:05,940
the one brought up during his hearing yesterday.

576
00:41:06,610 --> 00:41:11,510
That company belonged to your mother,
Inspector Han, right?

577
00:41:15,780 --> 00:41:18,450
This was the testimony
I gave to my dear Ji Hwa...

578
00:41:18,450 --> 00:41:20,060
and her minion.

579
00:41:20,760 --> 00:41:23,690
Oh Il Construction was the first
to make a bid...

580
00:41:23,860 --> 00:41:27,430
to be the constructor
of Munju's development we planned.

581
00:41:27,630 --> 00:41:30,100
Han Gi Hwan, the superintendent of that time,

582
00:41:30,100 --> 00:41:33,300
offered to come and grab a drink
just to see me.

583
00:41:33,540 --> 00:41:36,610
I figured he was going to bribe me
to help out his wife's company.

584
00:41:37,210 --> 00:41:40,940
Back then, your mother's company
wasn't in a good shape,

585
00:41:40,940 --> 00:41:44,550
like a lamp faced with a wind.

586
00:41:46,780 --> 00:41:47,820
And?

587
00:41:48,350 --> 00:41:51,790
And just as I expected,
he asked me to do him a favour...

588
00:41:54,660 --> 00:41:56,220
and drop her company.

589
00:41:59,490 --> 00:42:01,630
- What?
- Inspector Han.

590
00:42:01,630 --> 00:42:03,370
You saw his hearing yesterday, right?

591
00:42:04,130 --> 00:42:06,200
He's an amazing guy.

592
00:42:06,670 --> 00:42:08,570
He's a police officer
who's unbelievably upright...

593
00:42:08,570 --> 00:42:10,740
back 20 years ago and even now.

594
00:42:11,970 --> 00:42:15,240
I was totally touched...

595
00:42:15,240 --> 00:42:16,910
when he said this yesterday.

596
00:42:17,110 --> 00:42:18,850
What did you just say?

597
00:42:19,180 --> 00:42:23,080
Did you say you want to know
why the suspect of the murders...

598
00:42:23,290 --> 00:42:25,150
in Munju killed all those people?

599
00:42:25,150 --> 00:42:28,260
And did you just say you want to know...

600
00:42:28,260 --> 00:42:29,420
the women's occupations?

601
00:42:30,090 --> 00:42:31,690
Why do you want to know that?

602
00:42:32,230 --> 00:42:35,330
Are you telling me to narrate the story...

603
00:42:35,330 --> 00:42:38,070
of that murderer in front of the entire nation?

604
00:42:38,670 --> 00:42:39,940
Listen.

605
00:42:40,070 --> 00:42:42,500
Taking someone's precious life is...

606
00:42:42,500 --> 00:42:45,040
the most brutal kind of crime
a human being can commit.

607
00:42:45,040 --> 00:42:48,340
We must never share
the back story of such criminals...

608
00:42:48,780 --> 00:42:50,810
no matter what the reason is.

609
00:42:51,010 --> 00:42:52,780
What I am saying is...

610
00:42:52,780 --> 00:42:55,350
we shall not let those people take the microphone.

611
00:42:55,350 --> 00:42:58,320
Goodness, the microphone was too close to him.

612
00:42:58,320 --> 00:42:59,490
His voice is ringing in my ears.

613
00:43:00,820 --> 00:43:03,430
Inspector Lee.
I think this is enough for today.

614
00:43:03,430 --> 00:43:06,700
- No, I don't think it's enough.
- I don't think so either.

615
00:43:07,560 --> 00:43:10,000
What happened on October 15 early in the morning.

616
00:43:10,500 --> 00:43:12,530
I haven't said anything about that yet.

617
00:43:13,400 --> 00:43:15,070
Okay. Go on.

618
00:43:17,770 --> 00:43:19,740
That day, Chief Superintendent Han...

619
00:43:19,740 --> 00:43:23,010
insisted I drop Oh Il Construction.

620
00:43:23,180 --> 00:43:26,050
He drank a lot until the next morning.

621
00:43:26,150 --> 00:43:28,850
He even tried to drive his car.

622
00:43:29,020 --> 00:43:30,490
So I...

623
00:43:33,990 --> 00:43:36,990
My goodness.
I told you I'll drive you home.

624
00:43:37,290 --> 00:43:40,630
Let him go.
He insists on driving back himself.

625
00:43:42,230 --> 00:43:44,030
I'm leaving too. Bye.

626
00:44:02,480 --> 00:44:04,390
I drove him home.

627
00:44:04,720 --> 00:44:06,720
You drove him home?

628
00:44:06,720 --> 00:44:10,060
Yes. Because I didn't drink much that night.

629
00:44:10,190 --> 00:44:12,860
Wait a minute. That night...

630
00:44:13,160 --> 00:44:15,360
someone did drive under the influence of alcohol.

631
00:44:16,730 --> 00:44:18,830
It was Councilwoman Do.

632
00:44:21,870 --> 00:44:23,000
Oh, right.

633
00:44:23,000 --> 00:44:26,340
Inspector Lee, didn't your sister disappear...

634
00:44:26,340 --> 00:44:27,780
early in the morning that day?

635
00:44:28,540 --> 00:44:31,480
I heard the injuries to her bones say...

636
00:44:31,480 --> 00:44:34,520
that she was in a car accident, right?

637
00:44:38,450 --> 00:44:41,690
You make it sound like
Councilwoman Do caused an accident.

638
00:44:41,690 --> 00:44:45,190
No, no. I can't be sure of that.

639
00:44:45,960 --> 00:44:49,730
But she did sell the deer farm to our company.

640
00:44:49,730 --> 00:44:52,470
Bodies of Kang Jin Mook's victims
were found at the place.

641
00:44:52,470 --> 00:44:55,500
So I was summoned by Ji Hwa many times.

642
00:44:55,500 --> 00:44:59,170
Jin Li Construction owned the property.

643
00:44:59,170 --> 00:45:01,380
But Councilwoman Do managed the place.

644
00:45:01,380 --> 00:45:03,580
I didn't even get the key to the place.

645
00:45:03,580 --> 00:45:06,280
I wonder how Kang Jin Mook got access...

646
00:45:06,280 --> 00:45:07,920
and buried the bodies there.

647
00:45:11,190 --> 00:45:12,520
Mr. Lee Chang Jin.

648
00:45:13,360 --> 00:45:15,920
If something happens to Councilwoman Do,

649
00:45:16,460 --> 00:45:18,890
won't it ruin your redevelopment project...

650
00:45:18,890 --> 00:45:20,600
in Munju?

651
00:45:20,700 --> 00:45:22,460
Why would it ruin the project?

652
00:45:22,460 --> 00:45:24,530
It's not like she's the mayor of Munju.

653
00:45:24,530 --> 00:45:26,900
She just owns a lot of land around there.

654
00:45:27,500 --> 00:45:30,540
So you think you don't need Councilwoman Do...

655
00:45:31,040 --> 00:45:33,880
to push the project forward.

656
00:45:33,880 --> 00:45:35,980
Come on. You can't put it like that.

657
00:45:36,440 --> 00:45:39,750
She needs to take some rest now.

658
00:45:40,080 --> 00:45:42,420
Her crazy son is in a loony bin.

659
00:45:45,720 --> 00:45:46,820
What?

660
00:45:46,820 --> 00:45:48,790
I'm talking about Park Jeong Je.

661
00:45:48,790 --> 00:45:50,960
He's a grown man
but he was dragged by his mother...

662
00:45:50,960 --> 00:45:53,160
and got locked up in a mental institute.

663
00:45:54,000 --> 00:45:55,900
Aren't you his friend?

664
00:45:56,430 --> 00:45:57,830
But you didn't even know about it?

665
00:45:57,830 --> 00:45:59,570
Gosh, how can you call yourself his friend?

666
00:45:59,570 --> 00:46:01,570
Just go get him out of there.

667
00:46:02,500 --> 00:46:05,540
I think that's enough for today.
You may leave.

668
00:46:06,340 --> 00:46:08,880
Seriously? Will you let me go as well?

669
00:46:10,610 --> 00:46:13,520
Yes. You'll be hearing from me again.

670
00:46:13,950 --> 00:46:16,720
Okay. Call me whenever you need me.

671
00:46:16,720 --> 00:46:19,350
I should help you
since you're Ji Hwa's friend.

672
00:46:20,660 --> 00:46:22,390
Thank you, Inspector Han.

673
00:46:26,530 --> 00:46:28,230
Gosh, my leg hurts.

674
00:46:34,100 --> 00:46:35,340
My goodness.

675
00:46:37,070 --> 00:46:38,340
Goodbye.

676
00:46:44,880 --> 00:46:46,450
Darn it.

677
00:46:46,920 --> 00:46:48,380
It was a magnificent show.

678
00:46:48,380 --> 00:46:50,550
But we weren't the leading roles.

679
00:46:50,550 --> 00:46:51,850
Lee Chang Jin...

680
00:46:52,490 --> 00:46:54,120
and Han Gi Hwan were.

681
00:46:55,820 --> 00:46:57,090
Maybe they...

682
00:46:58,390 --> 00:47:00,660
decided to leave Councilwoman Do out.

683
00:47:09,700 --> 00:47:11,210
(Park Jeong Je)

684
00:47:13,510 --> 00:47:16,440
The number you dialled does not exist.

685
00:47:16,540 --> 00:47:18,310
Please check and try again.

686
00:47:18,310 --> 00:47:20,680
Hi. I need to find someone.

687
00:47:20,680 --> 00:47:22,520
Someone who's admitted to a mental institute.

688
00:47:22,520 --> 00:47:24,590
I'll text you his personal information.

689
00:47:24,590 --> 00:47:26,320
Find him as soon as possible.

690
00:47:26,960 --> 00:47:28,120
Father?

691
00:47:29,960 --> 00:47:31,990
Tell him.
It doesn't matter if he knows.

692
00:47:32,860 --> 00:47:34,230
Who was that?

693
00:47:34,400 --> 00:47:36,200
He's a prosecutor
from Munju District Prosecutors' Office.

694
00:47:36,460 --> 00:47:38,370
He's actually a lot like my father.

695
00:47:39,100 --> 00:47:40,540
He's like a son to my father.

696
00:47:45,340 --> 00:47:48,180
Why do you think they decided to leave her out?

697
00:47:48,180 --> 00:47:51,280
Why did he have to tell us about Jeong Je?

698
00:47:51,680 --> 00:47:54,820
It seems like he's trying to stall us.

699
00:47:58,020 --> 00:47:59,650
Inspector Lee, I think Superintendent Jung...

700
00:47:59,650 --> 00:48:02,320
Hey, are you keeping your eye on Jung Cheol Mun?

701
00:48:02,990 --> 00:48:04,590
So where are you right now?

702
00:48:14,070 --> 00:48:15,200
He's in the office.

703
00:48:15,200 --> 00:48:17,540
- Did anyone else go in?
- No one.

704
00:48:22,080 --> 00:48:24,680
Sir, this is Oh Ji Hwa. Are you inside?

705
00:48:27,350 --> 00:48:28,580
Sir?

706
00:48:37,390 --> 00:48:39,060
Inspector Han.

707
00:48:39,760 --> 00:48:41,700
Inspector Lee. Why are you all here?

708
00:48:41,700 --> 00:48:42,860
(Head of Munju Police Station Jung Cheol Mun)

709
00:48:43,330 --> 00:48:45,770
Are you going somewhere?

710
00:48:47,070 --> 00:48:48,700
Oh dear.

711
00:48:48,700 --> 00:48:50,610
Haven't you heard from your father?

712
00:48:51,170 --> 00:48:54,110
I thought I won't be able to
go back to the Police Agency.

713
00:48:54,610 --> 00:48:56,080
But Chief Superintendent Han...

714
00:48:56,080 --> 00:48:58,510
assigned me to the intelligence department there.

715
00:49:00,580 --> 00:49:03,480
I guess we do not know what may happen tomorrow.

716
00:49:03,650 --> 00:49:05,150
Don't you think so, Inspector Lee?

717
00:49:13,560 --> 00:49:16,230
Inspector Oh, thank you for everything.

718
00:49:16,600 --> 00:49:19,670
I'll talk to the others
when I'm officially assigned.

719
00:49:19,670 --> 00:49:21,470
Let's keep it between us until then.

720
00:49:21,640 --> 00:49:22,870
Certainly, sir.

721
00:49:23,270 --> 00:49:24,840
I'll drive you there.

722
00:49:24,840 --> 00:49:27,710
Okay. You know where the Geumya Housing Area is, right?

723
00:49:27,710 --> 00:49:30,210
- Yes, sir.
- Do Su, drive safely.

724
00:49:30,410 --> 00:49:32,480
- This way, sir.
- Thank you.

725
00:49:34,250 --> 00:49:38,120
Inspector Han,
you know blood is thicker than water, right?

726
00:49:39,620 --> 00:49:42,090
Don't you forget that, all right?

727
00:49:44,930 --> 00:49:46,490
Good night, sir.

728
00:49:54,970 --> 00:49:57,370
- I'll follow the car.
- I'll go with you.

729
00:49:58,210 --> 00:50:00,240
Inspector Lee, wait.

730
00:50:00,740 --> 00:50:02,210
(Kwon Hyeok)

731
00:50:03,080 --> 00:50:05,950
Yes. Did you find him?

732
00:50:06,550 --> 00:50:07,750
Where?

733
00:50:08,820 --> 00:50:10,150
The outskirts of Munju?

734
00:50:12,690 --> 00:50:14,920
The outskirts of Munju?
What is he talking about?

735
00:50:14,920 --> 00:50:17,460
Ji Hwa, go on ahead.
I'll catch up with you.

736
00:50:18,760 --> 00:50:20,730
Okay. I'll see you later.

737
00:50:23,970 --> 00:50:25,370
Where are you right now?

738
00:50:29,880 --> 00:50:31,320
Where are you right now?

739
00:50:34,360 --> 00:50:37,860
Right now? I'm at home.

740
00:50:39,160 --> 00:50:41,060
You can text him now.

741
00:50:47,640 --> 00:50:49,300
Come to my house in Seoul right now.

742
00:50:53,040 --> 00:50:56,380
Han Ju Won. Hey. Hello? Hello?

743
00:50:57,040 --> 00:50:58,210
(Han Ju Won)

744
00:51:02,950 --> 00:51:06,150
Inspector Lee, may I use your phone?

745
00:51:06,150 --> 00:51:08,560
My battery went dead
so I couldn't get the location.

746
00:51:11,690 --> 00:51:12,930
Thank you.

747
00:51:23,000 --> 00:51:24,210
Hello?

748
00:51:24,940 --> 00:51:26,410
Give me the location.

749
00:51:27,640 --> 00:51:30,210
Suwon Nursing Hospital
in Munju, Gyeonggi Province.

750
00:51:30,810 --> 00:51:33,880
- Okay.
- Whose phone is this?

751
00:51:33,880 --> 00:51:36,680
You're not at home.
You're with Father, aren't you?

752
00:51:36,680 --> 00:51:38,420
What are you talking about?

753
00:51:40,250 --> 00:51:41,420
Actually, yes.

754
00:51:41,420 --> 00:51:45,190
(Cheong Wa Dae Civil Affairs' Office)

755
00:51:49,030 --> 00:51:50,230
Yes.

756
00:51:52,500 --> 00:51:56,370
Yes? I'll do my best.
Thank you very much, sir.

757
00:51:56,740 --> 00:51:58,340
- This is it.
- He made it.

758
00:51:58,340 --> 00:51:59,470
Congratulations, Commissioner General.

759
00:51:59,470 --> 00:52:00,610
Congratulations.

760
00:52:00,610 --> 00:52:02,100
(Nomination of Commissioner General
will be confirmed tomorrow morning.)

761
00:52:02,840 --> 00:52:04,710
Hey, Han Ju Won. Come quickly.

762
00:52:04,710 --> 00:52:06,850
Your father just got appointed
as Commissioner General.

763
00:52:12,990 --> 00:52:14,260
- I knew you would make it.
- Thank you.

764
00:52:14,260 --> 00:52:15,260
I had faith.

765
00:52:16,720 --> 00:52:17,790
Congratulations.

766
00:52:18,190 --> 00:52:19,260
Thank you.

767
00:52:19,690 --> 00:52:20,930
I'll do my best.

768
00:52:22,400 --> 00:52:23,530
I made it.

769
00:52:30,670 --> 00:52:33,240
Inspector Lee Dong Sik,
this is Jung Cheol Mun.

770
00:52:33,710 --> 00:52:37,310
I have something to say.
Come to my place alone quietly right now.

771
00:52:38,510 --> 00:52:39,510
"Alone".

772
00:52:41,680 --> 00:52:42,750
"Quietly".

773
00:52:53,890 --> 00:52:57,430
They said Park Jeong Je is
in Suwon Care Hospital in Munju.

774
00:53:00,600 --> 00:53:01,700
Let's go.

775
00:53:04,670 --> 00:53:05,740
Inspector Lee.

776
00:53:09,410 --> 00:53:10,610
I can't go.

777
00:53:11,480 --> 00:53:12,510
Why not?

778
00:53:15,620 --> 00:53:19,720
He got appointed as Commissioner General just now.

779
00:53:23,220 --> 00:53:24,690
He wants me to come home right now.

780
00:53:25,290 --> 00:53:26,460
I'll go there first.

781
00:53:26,960 --> 00:53:29,630
Hurry and go to Jeong Je.

782
00:53:29,630 --> 00:53:30,900
I'll contact you.

783
00:54:27,990 --> 00:54:30,520
(Geumya Housing Area)

784
00:54:44,170 --> 00:54:46,140
You know where the Geumya Housing Area is, right?

785
00:54:51,250 --> 00:54:53,380
Han Ju Won, what on earth have you done?

786
00:54:56,580 --> 00:54:59,690
Your wife works at
Crime Scene Investigation Department at Munju?

787
00:55:00,150 --> 00:55:01,190
Yes, sir.

788
00:55:01,460 --> 00:55:02,920
I heard your wife is due as well.

789
00:55:03,420 --> 00:55:05,290
Don't stand in the wrong line...

790
00:55:05,290 --> 00:55:06,960
and make your wife and your child suffer.

791
00:55:06,960 --> 00:55:08,760
I'm standing in the right line, sir.

792
00:55:10,400 --> 00:55:11,800
What are you doing?
You should get going.

793
00:55:15,270 --> 00:55:16,340
Yes, sir.

794
00:55:51,940 --> 00:55:53,870
- Did you get him home?
- Yes.

795
00:55:54,040 --> 00:55:55,110
Get in the car.

796
00:56:12,290 --> 00:56:15,500
(Geumya Housing Area)

797
00:56:36,080 --> 00:56:37,220
Inspector Han Ju Won.

798
00:56:38,090 --> 00:56:40,790
Did you take him inside the house?

799
00:56:41,190 --> 00:56:42,260
Yes.

800
00:56:42,460 --> 00:56:45,230
I helped him with his belongings and left the house.

801
00:56:47,600 --> 00:56:49,160
When was the light turned off?

802
00:56:49,160 --> 00:56:51,200
Not long ago. Why?

803
00:56:52,200 --> 00:56:54,600
I'll have a look for a moment.
Is that all right?

804
00:56:54,600 --> 00:56:55,970
- I'll go with you.
- No.

805
00:56:57,100 --> 00:56:59,270
I'll just have a look and come right back.

806
00:57:43,420 --> 00:57:45,550
- Do Su.
- Yes.

807
00:57:45,720 --> 00:57:46,890
I think we should go.

808
00:57:52,790 --> 00:57:54,160
(Geumya Housing Area)

809
00:58:11,810 --> 00:58:13,080
Han Ju Won came here, right?

810
00:58:13,080 --> 00:58:14,720
You didn't send him here?

811
00:58:16,250 --> 00:58:17,380
Where is he?

812
00:58:17,380 --> 00:58:20,350
Well... Did he lock the door inside?

813
00:58:20,820 --> 00:58:22,090
Is the door inside open?

814
00:58:34,340 --> 00:58:35,740
Han Ju Won.

815
00:58:44,750 --> 00:58:46,210
Superintendent Jung Cheol Mun.

816
00:58:50,280 --> 00:58:51,690
He's dead.

817
00:59:24,250 --> 00:59:25,420
I think...

818
00:59:27,090 --> 00:59:28,590
I killed him.

819
00:59:31,290 --> 00:59:33,430
- Do Su. Search around the place.
- Yes, ma'am.

820
01:00:21,680 --> 01:00:22,980
=Beyond Evil=

821
01:00:23,240 --> 01:00:25,380
Do you want me to deal with your son?

822
01:00:25,380 --> 01:00:28,050
The one with less power should act like one.

823
01:00:28,450 --> 01:00:29,720
That foolish guy.

824
01:00:30,250 --> 01:00:32,050
I can't let him go alone.

825
01:00:32,050 --> 01:00:34,620
- Are you sure it's Kang Jin Mook?
- Yes.

826
01:00:34,620 --> 01:00:37,620
Keep holding onto it
and get thrown on the ground together.

827
01:00:37,620 --> 01:00:39,560
Or let go of it when you have a chance.

828
01:00:40,090 --> 01:00:41,830
Take a break for a while.

829
01:00:41,830 --> 01:00:43,560
I'll take care of it.

830
01:00:46,270 --> 01:00:49,070
Do you think Jeong Je can handle it?

831
01:00:50,100 --> 01:00:51,570
I'm sorry, Dong Sik.

832
01:00:51,570 --> 01:00:53,170
Can you ask my mom about it?

833
01:00:54,910 --> 01:00:56,110
Jin Mook.

834
01:00:56,110 --> 01:00:59,380
The one who committed the crime
should be the one who pays for it.

835
01:01:00,510 --> 01:01:01,750
Ju Won.
